# How to create notes with color-coded snippits
Instructions on how to create "fenced code block" by using three backticks

### My Code Example
I learned how to use f-strings today:

```python
name = "Kadi"
print(f"Hello, {name}!") # This will be color-coded automatically

### Quick Markdown Cheat Sheet for Notes
Since you are new to this, here are the four most common "tools" you'll use to organize your thoughts:

| Markdown Feature | What you type | What it does |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Header** | `# Main Topic` | Creates a large title |
| **Sub-Header** | `### Sub Topic` | Creates a smaller section title |
| **Bullet Points** | `* Item` | Creates an organized list |
| **Inline Code** | `` `print()` `` | Highlights a single command in the middle of a sentence |
